    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think this would be possible, though I think the running time might be too long? (create 2 envs & run all tests). but I don't run the full suite very often. but yes this would be nice (and ideally we could have multiple benchmark runs say versus 0.19.0, 0.18.0) etc.\r\n\r\nwe could easily just setup another repo, like [dask](https://github.com/dask/dask-benchmarks) did recently. To make this pretty automated. (we *might* actually want to setup a new org, e.g. pandas-dev-benchmarks), because then the travis runs don't compete with main pandas, but that is a separate issue.\r\n\r\nnote that the actually running of the scripts is [here](https://github.com/dask/dask-benchmarks/tree/cron/cron), a set of automated scripts create an env and run it (this is the part that would go on travis).\r\n\r\nAlso someone could scour travis for tools / examples that does this kind of benchmarking.\r\n\r\nanyone want to give a whirl?"
  },
