    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> From observation travis runtimes can be very flaky which might greatly reduce the value of ASV results.\r\n\r\nThe question then is also if this difference is mainly between runs, or also during one run. As differences between runs is not necessarily a problem for this use case, as the benchmark always compares to master within the same travis run. \r\nBut I can certainly imagine that also this can be flaky.\r\n\r\nFor full benchmark results over time, this will indeed be a problem. But for this, another option would be to have a separate machine to do this (spend some money on this, or share infrastructure with other projects, https://github.com/dask/dask-benchmarks/issues/3#issuecomment-258282051)"
  },
